AD_FIELD.NAME: Keep Fixed Amount
AD_FIELD.HELP: Allows to keep a fixed amount in the current financial account.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A value defining what sequence and process setup are used to handle this document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Document Type determines document sequence and processing rules

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A fast method for finding a particular record.
AD_FIELD.HELP:
A search key allows for a fast method of finding a particular record. If you leave the search key empty, the system automatically creates a numeric number originating from a document sequence defined in the "Document Sequence" window. The sequence naming convention follows a rule "DocumentNo_TableName", where TableName is the actual name of the database table (e.g. C_Order).
Usually, company's internal identifiers for various records (products, customers, etc) are stored here.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Time to incrementally refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_FIELD.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every incremental refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The incremental refresh is much lighter, less expensive and therefore can be completed quicker than a total refresh, but will not detect deletions of master data records.
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.

AD_FIELD.NAME: G/L Item for Cash drop/deposit
AD_FIELD.HELP: In case of automated funds movement in cash up process, two new transactions for this movement are created both in current and destination financial accounts. These transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document type for Reconciliations
AD_FIELD.HELP: When Cash Up process is executed from POS, a reconciliation including all transactions done in that terminal since last cash up is created. This is the document type used for that reconciliation.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Group orders in one Invoice
AD_FIELD.HELP: In the cash up process, orders without invoice are grouped in one invoice per business partner.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Allow Deposits
AD_FIELD.HELP: When deposits are allowed, it will be possible for POS users to deposit money in current financial account through Cash Management process.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a payment type
AD_FIELD.HELP: A descriptive identifier of a payment type that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Allow Withdrawals
AD_FIELD.HELP: When withdrawals are allowed, it will be possible for POS users to drop money from current financial account from Cash Management process.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Payment Provider
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: External payment provider who processes this kind of payment types.
AD_FIELD.HELP: External payment provider who processes this kind of payment types.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: JSON order data
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: JSON object sent from POS terminal
AD_FIELD.HELP: POS terminal serializes tickets in JSON format to be sent to back end.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Line No.
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A line stating the position of this request in the document.
AD_FIELD.HELP: Indicates the unique line for a document. It will also control the display order of the lines within a document.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Refund Provider
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: External payment provider who processes this kind of refund types.
AD_FIELD.HELP: External payment provider who processes this kind of refund types.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Type
AD_FIELD.HELP:
Document type used for regular sales orders generated in back end from POS tickets.
Document Types determine document sequence and processing rules.

AD_FIELD.NAME: G/L Item for Withdrawals
AD_FIELD.HELP: When creating a withdrawal, two transactions are created: one in current financial account to take out the amount and another one in the destination financial account to deposit it there. Both of these transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Clear error
AD_FIELD.HELP: Once the error has been fixed and saved again, it is possible to remove it from the table by executing this process.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Send Email
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this order is going to be sent by email.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A flag indicating whether this order is going to be sent by email. This option belongs to Web POS.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Grouped Product
AD_FIELD.HELP: Grouped Product

AD_FIELD.NAME: Cash Up Event
AD_FIELD.HELP: Event triggered by Cash Up process in case the are founds transfer. This event defines the financial account the founds are transferred to.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Document Type for Returns
AD_FIELD.HELP:
Document type used for return orders generated in back end when a POS ticket is marked to be returned.
Document Types determine document sequence and processing rules.

AD_FIELD.NAME: G/L Item for Deposits
AD_FIELD.HELP: When creating a deposit, two transactions are created: one in current financial account deposit the amount and another one in the origin financial account to take it out from there. Both of these transactions will use this G/L Item.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Email Status
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The Email Status indicates the status of sending email.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Email Status indicates the status of sending email. To change the status of sending email, complete the order in Web POS application.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Time to fully refresh masterdata (in minutes)
AD_FIELD.HELP:
This field allows the user to specify the interval of time between every refresh of the master data (which includes business partners, products, tax information, ...). This time is specified in minutes.
The total refresh can be a very expensive operation, and if done too much frequently it can tax the server, and decrease the performance of all POS terminals, so it is strongly recommended to set it to a high value (60 minutes, or greater if possible).
So, if this field is set to 60, the master data will be refreshed every 60 minutes, if the user is logged in.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Cash differences
AD_FIELD.HELP: This is the G/L Item used in Cash Up process in case there are differences between the expected and counted amount in this payment type. In this case a new transaction with this G/L Item and difference between expected and counted amounts will be created.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Default POS Role
AD_FIELD.HELP: Role to be used by default in Web POS. This role must have access to Web POS form.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Name
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A non-unique identifier for a payment type
AD_FIELD.HELP: A descriptive identifier of a payment type that is used as a default search option along with the search key (that is unique and mostly shorter).

AD_FIELD.NAME: Open drawer before closing ticket
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag which define if we want to open drawer before paying ticket
AD_FIELD.HELP: A flag which define if we want to open drawer before paying ticket

AD_FIELD.NAME: POS Terminal Type
AD_FIELD.HELP: A POS Terminal Type configures all generic settings that can be used by different POS Terminals. Each of these terminals defines the specific settings.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Financial Account
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Financial account used to deposit / withdrawal money such as bank accounts or petty cash
AD_FIELD.HELP: Financial account used to deposit / withdrawal money such as bank accounts or petty cash

AD_FIELD.NAME: Default Your Company POS Login Image
AD_FIELD.HELP: Image that will be shown in the POS login window. If it is not set, it will be used the default one set in "System Info" window in the field "Default Your Company Login Image"

AD_FIELD.NAME: Order Document No Prefix
AD_FIELD.HELP: Each terminal needs to define a unique prefix to be added to the sales order document numbers generated from POS tickets making them unique.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Show stock screen
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: If this flag is active a intermediate screen will appear in web pos when the product is added to the ticket. The screen will inform about the stock of the product
AD_FIELD.HELP: If this flag is active a intermediate screen will appear in web pos when the product is added to the ticket. The screen will inform about the stock of the product

AD_FIELD.NAME: Automate Movement to Other Account
AD_FIELD.HELP:
When this field is flagged, Cash Up process will transfer founds from the financial account in this payment method to the one defined in the close event. In case it is not flagged, Cash Up process will create a reconciliation but will keep all the amount in current financial account.
If checked, different options on how to do this movement can be defined by setting the rest of fields in this group.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Payment Method
AD_FIELD.HELP: Generic POS Terminal payment method which defines the generic settings for it, such as payment method (card, cash...) and cash up and cash management settings.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Save again
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Try to process the order again
AD_FIELD.HELP: After fixing the data, the order can be processed again. Depending on the error, to fix the data can require to edit the JSON data to adjust it, or to properly set up configuration.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Allow Variable Amount
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Allow to keep a variable amount
AD_FIELD.HELP: When checked, it will include in the cash up process the option to allow user to manually define the amount to be kept in current financial account.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Allow Move Everything
AD_FIELD.HELP: Includes an option in cash up process to move everything from current financial account, so cash up process would set it to 0.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Error
AD_FIELD.HELP: It is the error message got when trying to import JSON data as an order.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Allow not to Move
AD_FIELD.HELP: Allows user to decide to keep all counted amount in current financial account.
